        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="TEXT-43af83ed-3771-49b8-b01f-9607ccd10445" LAST-CHANGE="2026-03-25T23:43:45Z">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="The level 3 low-level requirements specification of StrictDoc (L3/LLR) is derived from StrictDoc&#x27;s L2 high-level (L2/HLR) requirements specification. The purpose of L3/LLR is to provide the lowest-level requirements from which StrictDoc&#x27;s source code can be directly implemented without further information.\n\nIt is at the L3 level that the StrictDoc requirements are specified for the actual software implementers, including both the StrictDoc developers and AI agents such as Codex. At the same time, the L2/HLR requirements provide the framework for the WHAT and WHY of the implementation instructions that are specified by this L3/LLR.\n\nNOTE: This specification level is under construction. Many L2/HLR requirements will be gradually moved to be here at the L3/HLR level.">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>TEXT_1d15d80707e54322b1ae4db7d3efafe9_ReqIF.Text</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>TEXT_1d15d80707e54322b1ae4db7d3efafe9</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
